-- Verbund Lowers Full-Year Profit Forecast on One-Time Costs, Sees 35% Drop
-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 2010-10-28T06:05:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/verbund-lowers-full-year-profit-forecast-on-one-time-costs-sees-35-drop.html
Verbund AG , Austria’s largest
utility, said it expects full-year net income to decline about
35 percent this year. It had previously expected a decline of 25
percent.  This is due to  “negative one-off effects in the financial
results,” it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Zoe Schneeweiss  at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  